h3. Summary

Live Search Macro is not suggesting results when anonymous access is enabled, but instead, a 401 ERROR is generated in Developer tools.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Create one Confluence space 
# Enable Anonymous access in Space permissions and Global permissions
# Create a service desk projects with a link to that knowledge base
# Modify the search permissions for Jira Service Desk to enable view access for all users
{panel}
(i)
Any active user can view pages in this space, including users who don't have a Confluence license. This was enabled through Jira Service Desk so people can view knowledge articles when raising a help request.{panel}
# Check the Space overview and search in Live search, notice that there are results suggested
# Logout/Open one incognito window and try to search in the Overview Live Search > notice that no result is suggested

h3. Expected Results

When enabling the anonymous permissions, Live search should suggest results for anonymous users

{code}

Request URL: https://troubleshootingcompany.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/searchv3/1.0/search?queryString=test&where=TS1&type=page&user=&pageSize=5&highlight=false&sessionUuid=0-0-0-0
{code}
{code}
queryString=test&where=TS1&type=page&user=&pageSize=5&highlight=false&sessionUuid=0-0-0-0
{code}

h3. Actual Results

When enabling the anonymous permissions, the Live search is returning a 401 error, because the REST API is adding the username anonymous which doesn't exist on the site.

{code}
Request URL: https://troubleshootingcompany.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/searchv3/1.0/search?queryString=test&where=TS1&type=page&user=anonymous&pageSize=5&highlight=false&sessionUuid=0-0-0-0
{code}
{code}
queryString=test&where=TS1&type=page&user=anonymous&pageSize=5&highlight=false&sessionUuid=0-0-0-0{code}

h3. Notes

The issue is not reproducible if the site doesn't have Jira Service desk enabled, in that case, the REST API value for the username is null and the search works as expected 

h3. Workaround
No known workaround until now

